# Frontend UX and Component Guidelines

Use this rule whenever generating or modifying frontend code in `web/src/**/*`.

- Follow `docs/frontend-ux-component-standard.md` as the primary UX/component standard.
- Reuse existing shared patterns/components first; avoid introducing parallel visual styles.
- Inline help must use `InfoTip`; do not create custom `?` hint buttons.
- Destructive actions must use unified in-page confirm modal patterns; avoid browser `confirm()`.
- Keep button/input style tokens consistent (`btn`, `ghost`, `primary`, `danger`, `inp`, `sel`).
- Prefer explicit trigger interactions for expensive actions (for example Enter-to-search).
- Ensure responsive behavior remains usable after UI changes.

If a change must diverge, state the reason and scope explicitly in the response.
